functions.label: validateQuery
description:
ES|QL validation public API
It takes a query string and returns a list of messages (errors and warnings) after validate
The astProvider is optional, but if not provided the default one from '@kbn/esql-validation-autocomplete' will be used.
This is useful for async loading the ES|QL parser and reduce the bundle size, or to swap grammar version.
As for the callbacks, while optional, the validation function will selectively ignore some errors types based on each callback missing.

children.label: description

children.label: declaration

children.label: examples
description: A list of examples of how to use the command. Displayed in the autocomplete.

children.label: types
description: Command name prefix, such as "LEFT" or "RIGHT" for JOIN command.

children.label: preview
description: Displays a Technical preview label in the autocomplete

children.label: hidden
description:
Whether to show or hide in autocomplete suggestion list. We generally use
this for commands that are not yet ready to be advertised.

children.label: validate
description:
This method is run when the command is being validated, but it does not
prevent the default behavior. If you need a full override, we are currently
doing those directly in the validateCommand function in the validation module.

children.label: suggest
description: This method is called to load suggestions when the cursor is within this command.

children.label: fieldsSuggestionsAfter
description: This method is called to define the fields available after this command is applied.

children.label: asSnippet
description:
Should the text be inserted as a snippet?
That is usually used for special behaviour like moving the cursor in a specific position
after inserting the text.
i.e. 'fnName( $0 )' will insert fnName( ) and move the cursor where $0 is.

children.label: kind
description: This is useful to identify the suggestion type and apply different styles to it.

children.label: detail
description: A very short description for the suggestion entry that can be shown on the UI next to the label

children.label: documentation
description: A longer description for the suggestion entry that can be shown on demand on the UI.

children.label: sortText
description: A string to use for sorting the suggestion within the suggestions list

children.label: command
description: Suggestions can trigger a command by id. This is useful to trigger specific actions in some contexts

children.label: rangeToReplace
description:
The range that should be replaced when the suggestion is applied

IMPORTANT NOTE!!!

This range is ZERO-based and NOT end-inclusive  [start, end)
Also, do NOT try to account for newline characters. This is taken care of later.
